nd then collapsed like an empty suit of clothes onto the grass in the narrow interstice between flower bed and castle wall. A wave of drowsiness came over him, and he tried to shake it off with a jerk of his shoulder. He had to hurry. She was waiting. He thought he heard her insistent whisper.…

He was unaware of how he had got up, gone indoors, and switched on the lights, bathing Luciani’s canvas in a warm sheen. The Venetian girl stood half-facing him, alive and three-dimensional. Her dark